{"id": "duc04-testb-13:2#8", "contents": "The Asian Games are a proving ground for the 2000 Olympics in Sydney, Australia, and many countries have sent reduced teams due to the Asian crisis. China's deputy head of delegation, Li Furong, stated that the main target is the 2000 Olympics, and the games are not just about winning gold medals, but about achieving world standards. The games feature 377 gold medals in 36 sports, including Asian specialties such as kabaddi and sepak takraw. The ceremony was a welcome distraction for Thais, who have been struggling with economic problems. As one spectator, Sakchai Pungsrinon, said, \"Thailand has many problems. Asia also has many problems. For two weeks, maybe we can forget about all these problems.\""}
